'''Art rock''' is a [[subgenre]] of [[rock music]] that aims to separate the genre from [[popular entertainment]],{{sfn|Campbell|2012|p=393}} with the term typically being applied as the middle ground between [[Corporate rock|mainstream]] and [[experimental rock]]. Art rock primarily draws influences from the wider [[art world]]  and [[Academic art|academia]] which includes [[contemporary art]], [[art music]], [[Avant-garde|avant-garde art]], [[experimental music]], [[avant-garde music]], alongside [[classical music]] and [[jazz]].

Critics have defined art rock as a "rejection" of rock music intended solely for the purpose of popular entertainment or [[dance music|dancing]].{{sfn|Campbell|2012|p=393}} The term was closely associated with a specific period beginning in 1966â€“67, which became influential to the development of [[progressive rock]].{{sfn|Jones|2008|p=49}}

